description:
Nothing brings out craftiness like a precious new baby. This plush pattern was originally created for my baby boy who spent many hours mesmerised by his hot air balloons floating along with little hand stitched clouds. 

The mobile pattern comes as a PDF (digital file) format and includes easy to follow, step-by-step instructions, diagrams and pattern pieces. Both metric and imperial measurements are included and the pattern is printable on US letter or A4 paper. 

Finished balloons measure 18cm (9") in height each with the whole mobile around 80cm (20") in length.

Material List:
------------------------------------------
Cotton fabric 	 {four x 20cm x 40cm/ 8 x 16" pieces}
White felt square  {20 x 20cm/ 8 x 8"}
Felt for baskets   {10 x 20cm /4 x 8"} 
Fusible webbing  {50cm/20” x 2.5cm/1” strip}
Dowel or twigs	{ 2 x 30cm/12” long, 9.5mm 3/8" diameter}
Embroidery perle 5 {2 skeins to match baskets}
Bio,recycled or poly toy fill {approx 250g}
Fabric scraps for bunting
Matching thread
------------------------------------------

Immediately following payment you'll receive an email with link to download the PDF file so you can get crafting straight away.


For more balloon inspiration visit the blog: http://craftschmaft.com/tag/hot-air-balloon/

Create your very own Baby Zilla with this PDF pattern.  Just one sock, some stuffing and felt and he's ready to demolish everything in sight!

The pattern includes complete instructions, diagrams and material list. It comes in PDF (digital) format that you'll be able to download directly after purchase and print to A4 or letter size paper (no scaling, sticky taping or tracing required). 

This project is very easy to follow for beginners and experienced crafters alike. Sock toys can be hand or machine stitched. The finished items are soft, cuddly and baby friendly (no small parts or choking hazards).

Material List:

One sock {adult size}
Black felt scrap {3 x 9cm/1 x 4"}
White felt scrap {3 x 5cm/ 1 x 2"}
Coloured felt for spikes {4 x 26cm/ 2 x 10"}
Needle and matching thread
Toy stuffing {100-200g/4-7oz}
